Garissa leaders have welcomed the World Bank funded North-Eastern Development Initiative (Nedi) saying it would improve lives and compliment efforts by devolved governments. Led by Governor Ali Korane, they met in Garissa town yesterday where they deliberated on the finer details of the project whose implementing funds of  $100 million (Sh10 billion) the National government has guaranteed the development of 24 marginalised counties across the country. The projects were expected to consume Sh120 billion and would cover Garissa, Lamu, Tana River, Isiolo, Marsabit, Wajir, Mandera, West Pokot and Turkana counties. The meeting was organised to brief the leaders on the “nitty gritty of the projects, their  location and the impact they will have on local communities.” National Assembly Leader of Majority  Aden Duale said the leadership in county was convinced that the projects would have positive impact on residents in the region. – KNA